        "title": "fix(telegram): avoid routine reply quoting",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nStops Telegram draft previews and default assistant guidance from causing routine replies to quote the triggering message. This keeps native Telegram quoting available when explicitly useful, without making the first streamed paragraph appear as an automatic reply.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Removed automatic `replyToMessageId` from Telegram draft stream creation.\n- Updated assistant output directive guidance to avoid routine `[[reply_to_current]]` usage.\n- Added coverage that Telegram draft streams do not receive an implicit reply target.\n- Updated prompt guidance test expectations.\n\n## Testing\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-telegram.config.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts` — 98 tests passed.\n- `node --import tsx -e \"...buildAgentSystemPrompt checks...\"` — prompt guidance OK.",
